postcontent:
Hammerli 208 S (2 stage trigger, adjustable trigger position) with 80 gm weight, 2 magazines.  Extra magazines, other barrel weights available with gun purchase (not available separately).  No box, papers.

This grip is strikingly beautiful.  However, the gun to which it is mounted is not available any longer.  The gun, if purchased, will be the  Gold lettered Hammerli 208 S in my other ad.  The GRIP also can be used on most of the 208 (non-S) models.  If desired, I have a few that can be offered with this grip.  Price with this grip is around $1100-1200 for a standard 208, depending on which 208 is used.  

FFL transfer only.  Please note, only means ONLY and that includes FOID card holders, police officers, police departments, CIA, DIA agents etc..  Requests for exceptions will not receive answers.

Also for note by ATF and Customs agents, this gun is NOT one of those stolen while in Customs custody or shortly thereafter a few months ago.  It was one of the few that was not stolen in that shipment.

If this is close but not quite what is wanted, I also have ambidex 208, 212, and 208S available with the "combat" type grips from Nill and Hammerli.  Grips are NOT for sale without the gun.  The 208 are in the 900-1100 range, the 212 from about 1000-1400 depending on details.  

FOR THE CURIOUS:

A SPECIFIC GUIDE to the 208 and 208 S with list of most of the versions available from me also has been prepared and IS AVAILABLE for download.  An email address is required for that, due to file size and format.  The RH 208 S are lower in price than this gun, and the 208 are much less.

The S model is significantly more expensive than the standard 208 due to rarity and popularity in the USA.  The basic design is very similar, but the S model has a 2-stage trigger (adjustable play and pull weight between stages), an adjustable trigger position (front to rear), an enlarged trigger guard to accomodate that freeplay in trigger position, a different trigger adjustment system than the older 208 guns, and as a result, easier access to the recoil spring for changing that if ever needed.

The 208 uses a single stage trigger that is not adjustable for position (but is adjustable for pull and resistance).  There are a number of versions of the 208 which differ in the magazine release (bottom vs side frame mount), presence or absence of a safety, presence of an external coarse adjustment for trigger pull weight, and detailed trigger design (some use the 215 trigger).

The S model has been very popular in competition, but has never "bettered" the scores attained by the 208.  

This gun is one of several target and "other use" pistols available, which are NOT listed on Armslist.  For a complete list and EXPERT'S SELECTION GUIDE to these guns, please email.  The guide and list are free.  Several such guides (catalogue raisonne, in the old terminology) are available.  One covers a number of target pistols, one focuses on Hi Standard Victors, and one is specific to the 208 and 208S.
